      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok, those make sense. i'll check with the floor team about the cycle count timing and the manual scanning process. \n\none more thing, looking at the numbers again, they are very consistent. it's almost like a tiny, steady drain on the stock every single time we do the count. if it's not a counting error, what else could cause such a small, regular loss that's hard to track?",
